Calls to law enforcement or the hotline must be documented on in incident report in the notification section.  You must document the date, time and who you spoke with.  If law enforcement, make sure that you get the name of the officer and a case number, if applicable.  If the hotline, you must get the name and ID number of the operator, as well as the reference number for the case.  Those additional details can be noted in the narrative or disposition of the incident report.

