«If a staff is not directly participating in the activity for its entire duration, do they line of sight of what is happening and are they in close enough proximity to respond if needed.
If the children want to watch a movie with the lights dimmed, staff should remain with them or have a clear line of sight off all from where they are positioned.  If staff is at all concerned then the lights stay on.
 Staff will adjust seating arrangements if residents are not being appropriate.
«Staff will to participate and supervise children if they want to build a fort and play.
Staff can ensure positive play and interactions amongst their children, as well as the safety of all. 
 
