08/30/2020,748.685(a)(3) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,11/11/2020,11/16/2020,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,"Two young children ran from the operation, staff were not aware that the two children had run away until another child informed them. The two children are young, the operation is in a high traffic area, one of the children had a history of high risk behaviors, and neither of the children were followed.","Staff members must be aware of the whereabouts of the children assigned to their group throughout their shift.  Any special supervision or safety plans should be noted in the shift change report and discussed in incoming/outgoing staff members.  
 
Staff should call for assistance from the CATT team, Campus Administrator, or other available supportive staff on duty at the early signs of escalating tensions or behaviors amongst the residents.  
 
When a child leaves the facility, if the staff is unable to follow without compromising staff to child ratio, they will ask support staff (as noted above) to conduct a grounds search (generally no longer than 15 minutes) and to check in with other programs staff to ensure they (the missing child) have not entered another building on campus.  When the child cannot be located or if the child is seen leaving the property, Boerne Police is to be notified immediately to file a runaway report.   
 
"
